 a classic bildungsroman: the tale of a naive young woman at the crossroads of a traditional, restrictive world and a modern one with its freedom, risks, and responsibilities.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aFiction. 4aWaterloo Region. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aMiriam Toews.  aamish.  acoming of age story.  adepression in Canada.  adepression in Ontario.  agreat depression.  ahousekeeper story.  akitchener waterloo.  arussian mennonite.  asaskatchewan mennonite.1 aBrandt, Di, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aBrandt, Di, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFinlay-Young, Jane, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aFinlay-Young, Jane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978155458101640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781554581016423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781554581016/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles